        "text": "Brad Smith joined Sullivan & Cromwell immediately after law school, and he was appointed Special Counsel in 2006. Over the last 25 years, his practice has included a wide range of commercial litigation and counseling, with emphasis on antitrust and financial services matters. Brad’s antitrust work includes substantive advice to clients in merger and non-merger cases, as well as compliance with the Hart-Scott-Rodino Act. He has represented technology, life sciences, financial services, transportation and industrial clients in dozens of M&A transactions collectively valued at over $400 billion."
